\section{Bond operator formulation\label{sec:quadratic}}

Bond operator theory\cite{1990_Sachdev,1994_Gopalan} is a useful framework for describing a valence bond solid phase and its spin-1 triplon excitations. The theory is built upon the bond operator representation of the spin operators ${\bf S}_{L,R}$ forming a valence bond.

text:
\begin{equation}
\label{eq:bond_op}
\begin{array}{c}
 S_L^{\alpha} = \frac{1}{2} \left( s^{\dagger}t_{\alpha} + t_{\alpha}^{\dagger}s - i\epsilon_{\alpha\beta\gamma}t_{\beta}^{\dagger}t_{\gamma} \right),
 \\
 S_R^{\alpha} = \frac{1}{2} \left( - s^{\dagger}t_{\alpha} - t_{\alpha}^{\dagger}s - i\epsilon_{\alpha\beta\gamma}t_{\beta}^{\dagger}t_{\gamma} \right),
\end{array}
\end{equation}

